inals & U.S. Open adjust up: Thursday final ratings|last=Rejent|first=Joseph|work=TV by the Numbers|date=June 14, 2019|accessdate=June 14, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190615014800/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/thursday-final-ratings-june-13-2019/|archive-date=June 15, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Murphy finally gets help after roaming around the woods from the night before. Determined to find out the fate of Max. Murphy visits Max's ex-girlfriend Jenny, to see if she has any info on Max's whereabouts. After realizing that Max isn't going to show up to Jenny's house, Murphy and Jess go to their favorite bar, where Max finally shows up. However, the reunion is short lived because Felix calls the police and has Murphy and Jess arrested for \"stealing\" the work van. While in jail Murphy and Jess get in a fight over Murphy's obbession over Tyson's death. Jess decides to temporarily move out. Felix has money issues regarding the check he used to buy Guiding Hope. Jules witnesses a video of someone planting evidence to try and framed Darnell. She comes clean to Dean about her relationship with Darnell, and Dean decides to try and help her find out who framed Darnell. Nia leaves prison.\n |LineColor       = 006161\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 12\n |Title           = Rollin' with the Homies\n |DirectedBy      = [[Janice Cooke]]\n |WrittenBy       = Flint Wainess & Yael Zinkow\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|6|20}}\n |Viewers         = 0.60<ref name=\"1.12\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/thursday-final-ratings-june-20-2019/|title='Holey Moley,' 'MasterChef,' all others unchanged: Thursday final ratings|last=Rejent|first=Joseph|work=TV by the Numbers|date=June 21, 2019|accessdate=June 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190621212413/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/thursday-final-ratings-june-20-2019/|archive-date=June 21, 2019|url-status