   = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|6|11}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = AE8BAE\n}}\n{{^|Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 23\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|6|18}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = AE8BAE\n}}\n{{^|Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 24\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 11\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|6|25}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = AE8BAE\n}}\n{{^|Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 25\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 12\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|7|2}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = AE8BAE\n}}\n{{^|Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 26\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 13\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|7|9}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = AE8BAE\n}}\n}}\n\nEpisodes of the second season include:<ref name=\"WGA\">{{Cite web |url=https://directories.wga.org/project/1159661/in-the-dark/ |title=In the Dark|website=[[Writers Guild of America West]] |access-date=March 1, 2020}} Episodes with a credit date in 2019/2020.</ref>\n<!--Do NOT add to the episodes table until it has been confirmed by episode numbers with a reliable source or the episodes have been released!-->\n\n* \"Sex, Money, Feelings, Die\" written by Flint Wainess\n* \"The Truth Hurts\" written by Malarie Howard \n* \"The Unusual Suspects\" written by Adrian A. Cruz\n* \"Deal Me In\" written by Ryan Knighton\n* \"The Straw That Broke the Camel's Back\" written by Jess Burkle\n* \"Codependence Day\" written by Amy Turner\n* \"How to Succeed in Business Without Really Dying\" written by Anna Fisher\n* \"Bad People\" written by Daniel Christopher Rogers\n* \"The Last Dance\" written by Chelsea Taylor\n* \"My Pride and Joy\" written by Yael Zinkow\n* \" Where Have You Ben?\" written by Karine Rosenthal\n\n==Release==\n===Broadcast===\n''In the Dark'' premiered on The CW at 9:00&nbsp;p.m. on April 4, 2019.<ref name=TCW_press>{{cite press release|title=\"In The Dark\" premieres Thursday, April 4|url=https://www.cwtvpr.com/the-cw/shows/in-the-dark/about|location=Burbank, CA|publisher=[[The CW]]|date=January 2019|access-date=19 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419185639/https://www.cwtvpr.com/the-cw/shows/in-the-dark/about|archive-date=April 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\nOn [[review aggregator]] [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the series holds an approval rating of 70% based on 10 reviews, with an average rating of 7.16/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"Perry Mattfield is compelling as an amateur sleuth ''In the Dark'', although the series' recycling of mystery tropes and questionable treatment of physical handicaps may leave some viewers with a dim impression.\"<ref name=\"Rotten Tomatoes\" /> On [[Metacritic]], it has a weighted average score of 54 out of 100, based on 6 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |title=In the Dark: Season 1 |url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/in-the-dark |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS]] |date=2019 |accessdate=April 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190419133127/https://www.metacritic.com/tv/in-the-dark |archive-date=April 19, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n<!--====Season 1====-->\n{{Television episode ratings\n| width     = 99\n\n| title1    = [[#ep1|Pilot]]\n| date1     = April 4, 2019\n| rs1       = 0.2/1\n| viewers1  = 0.87<ref name=\"1.01\"/>\n| dvr1      = 0.1\n| dvrv1     = 0.35\n| total1    = 0.3\n| totalv1   = 1.22<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/live7-ratings-week-of-april-1-this-is-us-season-3-finale-1203194579/|title=Live+7 Ratings for Week of April 1: 'This Is Us' Season 3 Finale Posts Solid Gain|last=Thorne|first=Will|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 22, 2019|accessdate=April 22, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190422221628/https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/live7-ratings-week-of-april-1-this-is-us-season-3-finale-1203194579/|archive-date=April 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n| title2    = [[#ep2|Mommy Issues]]\n| date2     = April 11, 2019\n| rs2       = 0.2/1\n| viewers2  = 0.72<ref name=\"1.02\"/>\n| dvr2      = 0.0\n| dvrv2     = 0.33\n| total2    = 0.2\n| totalv2   = 1.05<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/live7-ratings-week-of-april-8-1203200773/|title=Live+7 Ratings for Week of April 8: 'Grey's Anatomy' Tops Scripted|last=Thorne|first=Will|date=April 29, 2019|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=April 29, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190430061719/https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/live7-ratings-week-of-april-8-1203200773/|archive-date=April 30, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n| title3    = [[#ep3|The Big Break]]\n| date3     = April 18, 2019\n| rs3       = 0.2/1\n| viewers3  = 0.64<ref name=\"1.03\"/>\n| dvr3      = 0.0\n| dvrv3     = 0.35\n| total3    = 0.2\n| totalv3   = 0.99<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/live7-ratings-week-of-april-15-1203206432/|title=Live+7 Ratings for Week of April 15: 'Good Girls,' 'New Amsterdam' Among Biggest Gainers|last=Thorne|first=Will|date=May 6, 2019|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=May 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190507015022/https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/live7-ratings-week-of-april-15-1203206432/|archive-date=May 7, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n| title4    = [[#ep4|The Graduate]]\n| date4     = April 25, 2019\n| rs4       = 0.2/1\n| viewers4  = 0.75<ref name=\"1.04\"/>\n| dvr4      = 0.1\n| dvrv4     = 0.30\n| total4    = 0.3\n| totalv4   = 1.05<ref>{{cite web|u