l of 4,427 confirmed cases with 683 discharged, as well as 10 confirmed deaths.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Yong |first1=Clement |title=Singapore coronavirus cases cross 4,000 with new daily high of 728 cases |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/singapore-coronavirus-cases-cross-4000-with-728-cases-in-new-daily-record |website=The Straits Times |accessdate=16 April 2020 |date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"16AprClu\">{{cite web |title=Links between Previously Announced and New Cases (16 April 2020) |url=https://www.moh.gov.sg/docs/librariesprovider5/pressroom/press-releases/annex-a_16-4.pdf |website=MOH |accessdate=16 April 2020 |date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThroughout the outbreak, several clusters were discovered; namely the Life Church and Missions Singapore, Yong Thai Hang health products shop, a business meeting at Grand Hyatt hotel,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/novel-coronavirus-3-new-cases-confirmed-all-have-not-recently-travelled-china|title=3 Novel coronavirus: 3 new cases confirmed, all have not recently travelled to China|date=9 February 2020|website=TODAYonline|access-date=9 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200210152715/https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/novel-coronavirus-3-new-cases-confirmed-all-have-not-recently-travelled-china|archive-date=10 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> the 10 Seletar Aerospace Heights construction site, the [[Grace Assembly of God]],<ref name=\"13FebMOH\">{{cite web |title=Eight More Confirmed Cases of COVID-19 Infection |work=MOH |url=https://www.moh.gov.sg/news-highlights/details/eight-more-confirmed-cases-of-covid-19-infection |accessdate=13 February 2020 |date=13 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200213114302/https://www.moh.gov.sg/news-highlights/details/eight-more-confirmed-cases-of-covid-19-infection |archive-date=13 February 2020 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Wizlearn Technologies (an e-learning firm at [[Singapore Science Park]]),<ref>{{c